President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Colorado due to wildfires that occurred between September 6 and November 5, 2020. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Jon K. Huss has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations. Further designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.